commit_message:
Add output service resolving support

Currently output-list and output-show have no
special API calls and resolved from stack.get.
Current changes add service methods list_outputs
and show_output and new API calls for outputs.

Change-Id: Id83f98dae9bc141053e059a10ae381f953a8fd50

commit_message:
Separate uploading packages for patching

- RPM packages are uploaded after Fuel admin node bootstrapped,
  as previous;
- DEB packages are uploaded after Fuel admin node deployed and
  'auxiliary' repository initialized.

Change-Id: I5c423529e175ef6ddfc9ac5f5e2359e1e0b6d32f
Closes-Bug:#1502242

commit_message:
Hive job type support on CI

Support hive job type on Sahara CI. Also using
datasources placeholders in output url for correct
work of job.

Change-Id: I1177a7d12e380b6eb032f6e6ba025aa86451d846

[{'created': '2015-10-08 15:31:08.000000000', 'message': "Fixing cluster creation without auto_security_group

If auto_security_group is disabled, but one or more
security groups is provided, cluster can't be created
and fails with yaml RepresenterError exception.

Change-Id: I294237c788c2d14d77f12e1a8d7e0dd60a6638bb
Closes-bug: #1504093
"}]
commit_message:
Fixing cluster creation without auto_security_group

If auto_security_group is disabled, but one or more
security groups is provided, cluster can't be created
and fails with yaml RepresenterError exception.

Change-Id: I294237c788c2d14d77f12e1a8d7e0dd60a6638bb
Closes-bug: #1504093

commit_message:
Enable anti_affinity feature in scenario test

Currently Anti_affinity feature is disabled in scenario test. We
enable this by changing the validate SCHEMA. It will be an array
of role strings.

Change-Id: I764f47b54418f173dc0fd4d2c8f0593d49059cb5

commit_message:
Fix issue with job types in Ambari plugin

Ambari plugin should return dictionary with
versions in job types method of Ambari plugin.
Closes-bug: 1502841

Change-Id: Icdfd1baf8543977c7f7c90847b6d75534a077d1b

commit_message:
Fix list-availability-zones API for PostgreSQL

Listing of availability zones using PostgreSQl does not work in Manila.
It is caused by usage of not strict types comparison.
So, fix it and add Tempest test for API.

Change-Id: I21a064d60c4e1ccb6752ba6e220785f80bd1cb69
Closes-Bug: #1506938
(cherry picked from commit 8c165b378958b541c5578303612dc9efa84076e6)

commit_message:
Fix share type model scalability for get request

"share type list" operation greatly depends on amount of records in
"shares" table. It leads to big slowness of just requesting list
of several records of share types. That can take dozens of seconds.

Main reason for it lays in usage of redundant "relationship" of "share
types" table to "shares" table. It is not used in Manila, so remove it.

Change-Id: I463b12e2eb7249b42835be063cd953b56ee7376d
Closes-Bug: #1506240
(cherry picked from commit f1ada3fe97942931c181ffe95df6233e3f3c9277)

commit_message:
Add -f option to formatting volumes for xfs

Support -f option only for xfs formatting.
This reverts commit 1b0ec1d0d66c6a79fbb31251be1164949106404f.
Closes-bug: 1506857

Change-Id: Iae25876ee134c710bfb0360e11d94a05cb1d6721

commit_message:
Add event logs for MapR plugin

MapR plugin now supports event logs. To complete
this task several additional changes were made:
1. Move node awareness checking from within configure_topology method
2. Add instances parameter to set_cluster_mode
3. Move topology map generation to cluster context
4. Move configs resolving to cluster context

Change-Id: Ic00b27f57eacf5664980358b7fd154632ef3f31e
Implements: blueprint mapr-event-log

commit_message:
Make Oracle Linux compatible with RDO

Oracle Linux isn't quite compatible with RDO because RDO
repo-files use $releasever which is 7Server.  The actual repo
location is /7/ instead of /7Server/.  This patch seds the
repo file in question.

Change-Id: I357d895d974e7c88386e673b791dfb3dc8d1e945
Closes-Bug: #1508127

commit_message:
Remove libs and extras.d usage from gate hooks

- Remove libs and extras installation in gates.

This helps to suppress warnings by devstack scripts.

Change-Id: I103639942edd8084a1de9185db720ddaa025d975

commit_message:
Use standard formatters for environment-create-session output

This commit adds usage of standard formatters for environment-create-session 
command's output instead of just 'printing' session id to the stdout
without any ability to parse it for example during automatisation of
CLI testing.

Closes-Bug: #1506560
Change-Id: I19bce3c2fe662002f4c5a24f9637514bce9ee39f

commit_message:
Sync httpd vhost settings in between pcmk and non-pcmk scenarios

Moves the vhost_params out of the manifest and into static hiera;
also removes unneeded server_alias parameter as that matched the
vhost servername anyway.

Change-Id: I4b5971b23ef3be9529a59075fa93ccc64af75b9c

commit_message:
Small refactoring of CLI tests for packages

- Removed running of local server from setUp method, because
actually it is needed only for one test
- Refactored 'import_package_by_url' method to allow it
import package not only by url
- Import package with half-random generated name and not with hardcoded
 "dummy_package", it fixes the problem of importing packages when tests
 run in a few threads, according to it, method "generate_name" was 
modified and now it uses "_" instead of "-", because package names 
now are generated via this method and "-" is prohibited for them.

Partially implements: blueprint cli-tests-coverage-improvement
Change-Id: I69d0c9f95fd5686cb184b2477bcba53862bb9f17

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary code in webhook logic

Previously we support policy actions which was also affecting the
webhook creation and triggering. This patch removes this support because
the relevant actions have been removed.

Change-Id: Ib4fe59958598fc3b1d5cb785dcc2f4d01d5f5fb7

section 'oslo_messaging_qpid' instead of 'DEFAULT'.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/liberty/config-reference/content/configuring-rpc.html
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/kilo/config-reference/content/configuring-rpc.html

commit_message:
Change section name for AMQP qpid parameters

According to docs for liberty and kilo [1,2] should be
section 'oslo_messaging_qpid' instead of 'DEFAULT'.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/liberty/config-reference/content/configuring-rpc.html
[2] http://docs.openstack.org/kilo/config-reference/content/configuring-rpc.html

Change-Id: I1160721f36768c33acb99407c107d23696cabe0f

commit_message:
Add batching for EDP jobs in scenario tests

Add field 'edp_batching' for run several job in
batches.
Batching - apportion jobs into batches. Jobs will be
runned and polled on several pieces in the batch.
closes-bug: #1508027

Change-Id: Idd3de8fb6f4b8c877937f6f9438dc344a31a8750

commit_message:
Switched CORS configuration to use oslo_config

When cors middleware was moved into paste.ini, genconfig was not
updated to indicate that the configuration method had changed.
This breaks backwards-compatibility, however since the middleware
supports automatic oslo config detection via pastedeploy, it is
easily corrected.

This patch updates the api-paste.ini file to encourage CORS
middleware to draw its configuration from sahara.conf. It also
moves cors to the beginning of the middleware pipeline.

Change-Id: I4cff577aeff21286d0f9ce13142babec39db5e13

[{'created': '2015-09-28 20:13:16.000000000', 'message': "Add freezegun to global requirements

Source: https://github.com/spulec/freezegun

PyPI: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/freezegun

This allows us to reproduce race conditions by controlling the clock in
third party libraries (such as PyPI/cryptography) which do not depend on
oslo_utils.timeutils (and thus cannot be controlled by timeutils' clock
freezing methods).

It allows you to universally freeze the clock when accessed via:

- datetime.datetime.now()
- datetime.datetime.utcnow()
- datetime.date.today()
- time.time()
- time.localtime()
- time.gmtime()
- time.strftime()

Using, for example, a context manager:

  with freezegun.freeze_time(datetime.datetime.utcnow()):
    pass

This is a proposed requirement of:

  https://review.openstack.org/#/c/227995/

Change-Id: I6daed50a9128f0c6208ed1d432177d2da0613e14
Related-Bug: 1473567

"}, {'created': '2015-10-06 20:32:48.000000000', 'message': "Add freezegun to global requirements

Source: https://github.com/spulec/freezegun

PyPI: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/freezegun

This allows us to reproduce race conditions by controlling the clock in
third party libraries (such as PyPI/cryptography) which do not depend on
oslo_utils.timeutils (and thus cannot be controlled by timeutils' clock
freezing methods).

It allows you to universally freeze the clock when accessed via:

- datetime.datetime.now()
- datetime.datetime.utcnow()
- datetime.date.today()
- time.time()
- time.localtime()
- time.gmtime()
- time.strftime()

Using, for example, a context manager:

  with freezegun.freeze_time(datetime.datetime.utcnow()):
    pass

Consuming projects
==================

This is a proposed requirement of keystone:

  https://review.openstack.org/#/c/227995/

I also believe it could be used to supplant oslo time_utils
limited implementation of the same behavior.

Is the library actively maintained?
===================================

Yes, the library is actively maintained by a small group of
contributors:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/commits/master

The latest release was August 2015.

Is the library good code?
=========================

The actual library is small, and although mostly undocumented, well
structured and easy to follow:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/blob/master/freezegun/api.py

The test suite is quite exhaustive and includes plenty of negative
tests, for example:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/blob/master/tests/test_datetimes.py

Is the library python 3 compatible?
===================================

freezegun claims compatibility with at least Python 3.3. It seems to
work in Python 3.4 for the use cases I've tested.

Is the library license compatible?
==================================

freezegun's LICENSE file:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/blob/master/LICENSE

Is the library already packaged in the distros we target?
=========================================================

freezegun is packaged for Ubuntu:

  http://packages.ubuntu.com/vivid/python-freezegun
  http://packages.ubuntu.com/vivid/python3-freezegun

... and for Fedora:

  https://apps.fedoraproject.org/packages/python-freezegun
  https://apps.fedoraproject.org/packages/python3-freezegun

Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries?
===================================================================

Other than oslo time_util's limited implementation, frozendate is the
other, seemingly less popular and less comprehensive option that I'm
aware of and that's not in openstack/requirements either.

Change-Id: I6daed50a9128f0c6208ed1d432177d2da0613e14
Related-Bug: 1473567

commit_message:
Add freezegun to global requirements

Source: https://github.com/spulec/freezegun

PyPI: https://pypi.python.org/pypi/freezegun

This allows us to reproduce race conditions by controlling the clock in
third party libraries (such as PyPI/cryptography) which do not depend on
oslo_utils.timeutils (and thus cannot be controlled by timeutils' clock
freezing methods).

It allows you to universally freeze the clock when accessed via:

- datetime.datetime.now()
- datetime.datetime.utcnow()
- datetime.date.today()
- time.time()
- time.localtime()
- time.gmtime()
- time.strftime()

Using, for example, a context manager:

  with freezegun.freeze_time(datetime.datetime.utcnow()):
    pass

Consuming projects
==================

This is a proposed requirement of keystone:

  https://review.openstack.org/#/c/227995/

I also believe it could be used to supplant oslo time_utils
limited implementation of the same behavior.

Is the library actively maintained?
===================================

Yes, the library is actively maintained by a small group of
contributors:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/commits/master

The latest release was August 2015.

Is the library good code?
=========================

The actual library is small, and although mostly undocumented, is well
structured and easy to follow:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/blob/master/freezegun/api.py

The test suite is quite exhaustive and includes plenty of negative
tests, for example:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/blob/master/tests/test_datetimes.py

Is the library python 3 compatible?
===================================

freezegun claims compatibility with at least Python 3.3. It seems to
work in Python 3.4 for the use cases I've tested.

Is the library license compatible?
==================================

freezegun's LICENSE is Apache 2.0:

  https://github.com/spulec/freezegun/blob/master/LICENSE

Is the library already packaged in the distros we target?
=========================================================

freezegun is packaged for Ubuntu:

  http://packages.ubuntu.com/vivid/python-freezegun
  http://packages.ubuntu.com/vivid/python3-freezegun

... and for Fedora:

  https://apps.fedoraproject.org/packages/python-freezegun
  https://apps.fedoraproject.org/packages/python3-freezegun

Is the function of this library already covered by other libraries?
===================================================================

Other than oslo time_util's limited implementation, frozendate is the
other, seemingly less popular and less comprehensive option that I'm
aware of and that's not in openstack/requirements either.

Change-Id: I6daed50a9128f0c6208ed1d432177d2da0613e14
Related-Bug: 1473567

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-10-21 09:10:25.000000000', 'message': "Use openstack/requirements for repeatable builds

Add this repo to the openstack-base image, and use the upper-constraints
to install the client packages. Will follow up with dependant patches
for the child images to reduce the risk of breaking everything at once.

--

Background:

Many dependencies in the requirements.txt of OpenStack components have
quite loose version requirements, in many cases they will just specify a
minimum version (e.g. WebOb>=1.2.3).

The result of this is that given a Kolla image for Keystone built today,
another build of the exact same ref of Keystone could be broken
tomorrow, due to it picking up a later unsupported dependency.

The https://github.com/openstack/requirements repo exists to bring some
sanity to this situation. (It also outlines other problems it solves in
it's readme).

This patch has stable/liberty instead of master.

Change-Id: Iccb4e99f8e4b6659a19c1817d0f4c697824af25c
Partial-Bug: #1505306
(cherry picked from commit 72a8f5aabd31079d6fe8f0442a487689b4ba7bde)
"}]
commit_message:
Use openstack/requirements for repeatable builds

Add this repo to the openstack-base image, and use the upper-constraints
to install the client packages. Will follow up with dependant patches
for the child images to reduce the risk of breaking everything at once.

--

Background:

Many dependencies in the requirements.txt of OpenStack components have
quite loose version requirements, in many cases they will just specify a
minimum version (e.g. WebOb>=1.2.3).

The result of this is that given a Kolla image for Keystone built today,
another build of the exact same ref of Keystone could be broken
tomorrow, due to it picking up a later unsupported dependency.

The https://github.com/openstack/requirements repo exists to bring some
sanity to this situation. (It also outlines other problems it solves in
it's readme).

This patch has stable/liberty instead of master.

Change-Id: Iccb4e99f8e4b6659a19c1817d0f4c697824af25c
Partial-Bug: #1505306
(cherry picked from commit 72a8f5aabd31079d6fe8f0442a487689b4ba7bde)

commit_message:
Image meta: treat legacy vmware adapter type values

Ensure that legacy metadata vmware_adaptertype values are
treated correctly. This value could have been set as "" and there
are existing deployments that use that.

Change-Id: I28e9ca9075f33ff19855408af02bc454780e7c79
Closes-bug: #1506465

commit_message:
Making parameters of job binaries create optional

'description' and 'extra' parameters of job binaries
create method should not be required.
This change doesn't break backward compatibility.

Change-Id: I11c4933961482c87508615c2f7fb58db8456efed
Closes-bug: #1508406

commit_message:
Package type plugins support was added

Adds support for package type classes in plugins.
As a result additional package types may be introduced
without changes to Murano source code

Implements-Blueprint: pluggable-package-types

It's the first time I hear this. We (I and Alexey) have our own opinions. Let me explain.

We decided to split the solution of this issue in 2 parts:

1) Fix API output - fixed by this RR

2) Get rid of task creation and fix the UI so it would rely on API output instead of task - this is quite a lot work.

Activity #2 is tracked by https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1507960 , which I created right after merge of this RR.

As for fuelclient, yes, that's my fault. We had plans to run client tast against RRs in fuel-web. I'll raise this topic in openstack-dev ML."}]

commit_message:
[Contributor Guide] Build locally section to RST

This patch:

- translates the below wiki pages to RST:
  https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/HowTo#Building_Output_Locally
  https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/HowTo#Using_Tox_to_check_builds
- reworks the content (removing outdated info).

Change-Id: Ieb0e09c8c98529b6f7413a49100d4c52150ef3dd
Implements: blueprint docs-contributor-guide

commit_message:
Fix usage of dependencies

Manila is broken is threee places, so fix them:
1) test 'test_misc' with WebOb 1.5

WebOb 1.5 was released at 2015-10-11. With this new version,
webob.exc.WSGIHTTPException() constructor now fails with a KeyError
when the HTTP status code is 0.

test_exceptions_raise() of test_misc tries to instantiate all
exceptions of manila.exception. The problem is that
ConvertedException uses a default HTTP status code of 0.

Modify the default HTTP status code of ConvertedException to 400 to
fix the unit tests.

2) Add dependency for 'testresources' that is required by migration
tests.

3) Remove 2 unit tests related to testing of oslo.policy lib
functionality that should not be tested in Manila. It started failing
because under-the-hood behaviour was changed in new realese 0.12.0

Closes-Bug: #1505153
Closes-Bug: #1505374

Change-Id: I0f28f3c3fb2c7eec1bafc3a617344990f86810cf
(cherry picked from commit 9c99814ce5943bd4c33bf3650b832666e31b3411)

Fix broken unit tests

With release of six module version 1.10.0 several our unit tests
started to fail because of usage of not strict constructions.

Changes:
1) Manila unit test
"manila.tests.share.test_api.ShareAPITestCase.test_extend_quota_error"
used str for int substitution. So, use int data for int substitution.

2) Module 'manila.share.drivers.hp.hp_3par_mediator' was using
LOG.exception function when no traceback were exist it led to
AttributeError on py34. So, replace all usages of 'LOG.exception'
with 'LOG.error' where no raised exceptions exist.

Change-Id: Ic5b37bfb9d939d03f6ff68bc53d134bf9e5f996e
Closes-Bug: #1503969
(cherry picked from commit f38b8d4efd1f68f4ea29747f7377e0936f61d89c)

From now on, a user is assigned to a project (tenant) through the

  }

commit_message:
Deletes tenant parameter from keystone_user

The tenant parameter was made deprecated in Kilo and to be removed in Liberty:
see bug/1472437 and corresponding patch.

This patch removes the tenant parameter from the keystone_user provider and the
manifests using it.

From now on, a user is assigned to a project (tenant) through the
keystone_user_role provider.

For instance,

When using the default domain:
  keystone_user_role {'user1@project':
    ensure => present,
    roles  => ['admin'],
  }

When using non default domains:
  keystone_user_role {'user1::domain1@project1::domain2':
    ensure => present,
    roles  => ['admin'],
  }

Change-Id: I79f1bca4c67a4c92234431b2ae867933172a1ebe

commit_message:
Fuel-stats prepared for OpenStack CI

We have 3 services: analytics, collector, migration.
Migration is frozen and going to be removed. Also
migration requires Elasticsearch server for tests,
thus it can't be tested on OpenStack CI.

Pep8 checked on all services.

Project works only on python2.7, thus
gate-fuel-stats-python26 should be removed.

Change-Id: Ic5b6f15903918b4b0850ce0cdc12543925de0cfa
Closes-Bug: #1500073

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within cinder module.

Change-Id: Ie211ad42163833830fbfe8bbf6c2671632394566

commit_message:
Adding Job Types support to CLI

Adding Job Types commands to Sahara
OpenstackClient plugin:

$ dataprocessing job type list
$ dataprocessing job type configs get

Partially implements: blueprint cli-as-openstackclient-plugin

Change-Id: I259b006dc47da92952cdc2289ce0af8c200b39ef

commit_message:
Adding Job Templates support to CLI

Adding Job Templates commands to Sahara
OpenstackClient plugin:

$ dataprocessing job template create
$ dataprocessing job template list
$ dataprocessing job template show
$ dataprocessing job template update
$ dataprocessing job template delete

Partially implements: blueprint cli-as-openstackclient-plugin

Change-Id: I8c93b26c6eca37dbb144d7184c4d07dbe15bd9ab

commit_message:
Adding Clusters support to CLI

Adding Clusters commands to Sahara
OpenstackClient plugin:

$ dataprocessing cluster create
$ dataprocessing cluster list
$ dataprocessing cluster show
$ dataprocessing cluster update
$ dataprocessing cluster scale
$ dataprocessing cluster delete

Partially implements: blueprint cli-as-openstackclient-plugin

Change-Id: Icbf1778f621f18a6e7deca7f093a31fa3ee1c5b7

commit_message:
Making parameters of job executions create optional

input_id, output_id, configs parameters of job execution
create method should not be required.
This change doesn't break backward compatibility.

Change-Id: I01fb2406264c671aa15351df834814d32d3275a6
Closes-bug: #1507966

commit_message:
Making parameters of job create optional

mains, libs and description parameters of job
create method should not be required.
This change doesn't break backward compatibility.

Change-Id: I9c90f86ea70217fe5e404e097cd6f9ec6a32fe58
Closes-bug: #1506448

commit_message:
Remove unused operatingsystem module

The operatingsystem module is not referenced by fuel-library and was
last updated in 2013. This change removes this module from the
repository.

Change-Id: Ie5e3e4b7d32bd852a3dd6dd1f927166deb479abc
Closes-Bug: #1508272

commit_message:
Add puppet jobs to fuel-library

This change adds the puppet lint, syntax and unit test jobs as
non-voting check jobs for fuel-library.

Change-Id: I16a53063e9b1af8d3cf6d38d9570fb271f1f35c7
Related-Bug: #1507751

commit_message:
Remove unused gerrit ACLs

gerrit/acls/openstack/swiftsync.config is unused. We have no
swiftsync repo in openstack, the one in stackforge is retired.

commit_message:
Remove redundant sections of tripleo job names

All the tripleo jobs are now using ironic, puppet and deploying
an overcloud so remove these parts of the jobs names as the no
longer serve any purpose distinguishing between jobs.

Change-Id: I4a891159f2313ec70651e4db45f57e0f9c778a31

commit_message:
Enable stable branches for tripleo repositories

Adjust the acls so the following repos allow branch creation,
administered by the tripleo-release group, with reviews of the
to-be-created stable/liberty branches handled by the existing
tripleo-core team (we're not planning a separate stable-maint
group at this point).

The following repos are affected:

* openstack/tripleo-common
* openstack/tripleo-docs
* openstack/tripleo-heat-templates
* openstack/tripleo-puppet-elements
* openstack/python-tripleoclient
* openstack/instack-undercloud

These now all share the common tripleo.config, with instack split
out to a seperate acl, as it does not currently require a stable
branch.

This is the first step to implementing the stable/release branch
process described in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/221811/

Change-Id: Ibd82864cc8d25acf0f8c425d13f1ccdffff50a31

commit_message:
Revert "Add hooks for external install & svc management"

This reverts commit b2f791400dd4d2ab5d68b933b24cd51f27b268c8.
This commit broke tripleo ci jobs as a dependency on an anchor
is failing.

Closes-Bug: #1507934

commit_message:
Create openstack/puppet-openstack-release-tools

We're currently using some scripts (Python, bash) that are located to
different gist or github places.

For consistency and to help Puppet OpenStack release process, we need a
repository where we could host our tools that will be used for release
management.

Change-Id: I6e40fe4758297f486c7f4344230dc1e30981b55b

commit_message:
Deletegate gerrit project ownership

The openstack-infra/gerrit project[1] tracks upstream Gerrit and also serves
as a fork which we use for review.o.o.  There is a gerrit-core group[2] but
it's not being used yet.  Change ownership of the project from infra-core
to gerrit-core so that we can delegate ownership to a subset of devs working
to maintain openstack's Gerrit.

[1] https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-infra/gerrit
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/admin/groups/921,members

Change-Id: Id022177dc9ebb8755f334ff02f1aa60e36578056

commit_message:
Add `npm shrinkwrap` to `npm run` macro.

The npm shrinkwrap command is equivalent to pip freeze,
as it captures current dependency versions and generates a
deterministic list in npm-shrinkwrap.json. This file is then output
to the console for informational purposes, however unless the
project explicitly includes it in package.json's "files" field,
it will not be included in the release package.

Change-Id: I17ad8653dfed873092b811c41c638ff0ed0eb45d

commit_message:
Include mysql and ambari-metrics-collector to Ambari images

Include mysql related packages to Ambari images, because we are using
that during creation/preparing Ambari cluster in sahara codebase (see
[0]).

Also, include ambari-metrics-collector as a part of Ambari.

[0] https://github.com/openstack/sahara/blob/master/sahara/plugins/ambari/deploy.py#L108-L123

commit_message:
Added support of Drill 1.2 to MapR images in sahara-image-elements

Images for the following MapR versions: 3.1.1, 4.0.1, 4.0.2, 5.0.0
support Drill 1.2

Change-Id: I1f3b765c5c0e87920a71ccf467d302330845e930
Implements: blueprint sie-mapr-drill-12

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within keystone module.

Change-Id: If775591f6798d06e6dfc2a042a0d21e331c912ff

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within nova module.

This patch also fixes the typo on s/neutron/nova/ for sqlite_package_name.

Change-Id: Ie978ad5c6bc82e07f2638f6ec722e2bbcb146449

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within ironic module.

Change-Id: Ib3071679d9d2f0bca12169c6ad66f45b5f9b6d1a

commit_message:
Show command output directly in package_utils.sh

No need to run command in a subshell then echo the output,
just run the command directly is enough.

Change-Id: I7863f164dc680d98f460e36f96f4189fc311add6
Signed-off-by: Zhao Lei <zhaolei@cn.fujitsu.com>

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within ceilometer module.

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within sahara module.

Change-Id: I1c9378fb9aba2b4261ab25f4057cccf71560d1a8

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within cookiecutter.project_name module.

Change-Id: Ide20504a8804ccda1698dbb477661db8af610423

commit_message:
Remove unused gettextutils from oslo-incubator

Now that the old config generator code has been replaced/removed
we can now also remove gettextutils.  The generator was the last
hold-out in our code still using that obsolete code.

This patch removes the unneeded file and also updates the i18n code
that was monkey patching in support for using the _() and _LX()
functions in gettextutils.

Change-Id: Ib29915b13bd7f0173637ac6d1881f1ca06b713d6
related-bug: 1381563

commit_message:
Add stevedore aliases for interface_driver configuration

Changed the interface_driver configure for agents from class
imports to stevedor aliases. The loading method needed to be
updated to load as a DriverManager. Backward compatability
for configuration as class import.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ic349691989484286cd7c60eaf3ad1454c5852d1f
Closes-Bug: #1504536

commit_message:
db: Use postgresql lib class for psycopg package

This patch introduce the same design than mysql for postgresql
by requiring dedicated lib::python class instead of declaring
a new resource package within murano module.

Change-Id: I827c58174f235c7e3fafd9701a5b2fad261f2c4f

commit_message:
Remove the port-forwarding sub-project from the list

This project is no longer maintained, there are newer talks
going on to better support the use case [1], possibly in
tree. To this aim, it's safe to remove this project from
the list.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-September/073461.html

Change-Id: Ic1ae39f19381bc912a5fdb6417fff19181916744

commit_message:
remove unused configuration options

AODH has nothing to do with collector_workers configuration option,
but devstack/plugin.sh still configures it, this is caused by
splitting from Ceilometer project but not cleaned very well.

This patch also removes an unused configuration option defined in
aodh/service.py named notification_workers. Maybe in future, the
event alarm needs some worker configurations, we can wait for
that but now let's remove it.

Change-Id: I5759551673175e2750e8ccc658494d8a04498809
DocImpact: an unused option notification_workers has been removed

commit_message:
Improve dry-ness of base dockerfile.j2

The delorean repositories no longer have a separate location for
openvswitch.  Now openvswitch is located in delorean-deps.repo
and the rest of delorean master is located in the delorean.repo
file.  These files can be installed for both RDO and SOURCE, but
not for RHOS.  This patch uses the install_metatype to make a
determination as to when to install these two repos.  In the
process, we can remove the source RPM installation.

Closes-Bug: #1508326
(cherry picked from commit c7a9835b683d0177c93dd2751ec9acb688e106f9)
Change-Id: Ieedddd9d7ee234b6acdb03f7043d57c18e024951

commit_message:
Do not make hard dependency on Anchor if their not part of the catalog

Currently, the way the anchors are specified means that the anchors
declared in init.pp must be part of the catalog
{mysql,postrgresql,sync}.pp are declared in. This is not always true
hence making the catalog compilation failing in those cases.

This commit aims to make the manifest respect those ordering if the
anchor resources are part of the catalog.

Change-Id: Ib7fa886e5dcc4cbf55b43aa6636e0c40aa3507a7
Closes-Bug: 1507934

commit_message:
Murano CI Rework: Update job definitions

 - Add new macros to macros.yaml
 - Replace job definitions with job templates
 - Add heartbeat jobs for all murano-related projects
 - Add coverage job for murano

commit_message:
In gate functional testing

This runs the ansible playbooks to completion.

It does not validate that OpenStack is working yet, but it will ensure
Ansible did not break.

Additional gates will be needed for this and there is a patch in
project-config to handle that.

Change-Id: I7a24a704023cc8f19d42844636e9cb512060f693
backport: liberty
Partially-Implements: blueprint functional-testing-gate
(cherry picked from commit f39bb2ee13a10d17d5ef1410489c9804fc1c014a)

commit_message:
Add anti-XSS horizon vhost options

New header values:
Header X-XSS-Protection "1; mode=block"
Header set X-Content-Type-Options nosniff
Header always append X-Frame-Options SAMEORIGIN

Disabled directory index listing.

Added spec for openstack::horizon

Fixed fixtures+git refs to run openstack::horizon
in rspec correctly.

Change-Id: I50eb6104134f98fa61283f8ddda7449f92e99783

[{'created': '2015-10-09 16:54:36.000000000', 'message': 'Simplify rpc_backend parameter

It is no longer necessary to specify the whole python namespace
for the backends, and
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.messaging/opts.html lists
the short versions.

This patch maintains backwards compatibility with the previous
default value in case it is explicitly used.

Change-Id: I33cf918e394bfed9e436a4a8c9efc1c1dcc2f22d
'}]
commit_message:
Simplify rpc_backend parameter

It is no longer necessary to specify the whole python namespace
for the backends, and
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.messaging/opts.html lists
the short versions.

This patch maintains backwards compatibility with the previous
default value in case it is explicitly used.

Change-Id: I33cf918e394bfed9e436a4a8c9efc1c1dcc2f22d

mistral-documentation: dashboard documentation regarding debug known issue

* added explanation how to resolve an unsuccessful login
upon debug/run session using pycharm

Implements blueprint:mistral-docs-dashboard-troubleshooting

commit_message:
Refactor _populate_ports_for_subnets for testability

I want to add to this function but I found it very difficult to test
the additions that I was making (because this code isn't well covered
by UTs).  This patch adds some unit testing so that I can change it
more confidently but does not change any functionality.

Change-Id: Id2cf57968f2dfb8bcf18946c922ce2bb51a27766
Partially-implements:  bp/address-scopes

commit_message:
Add build profiles to build.py

Add ability to define "profiles" in kolla-build.conf, which are
predefined sets of images to build at once.

The supplied profiles match what Steven defined in the
restructure-template bp, though others can easily be added by the user.

Multiple profiles can be supplied at once, as well as supplemented by
the existing regex mechanism, e.g. to build profiles infra, main, and
also ironic, one can use:

tools/build.py --profile infra --profile main ironic

Change-Id: I0c6f450152cb23dcfc58e0969669fcedf03fab01
Implements: bp restructure-template
Doc-Impact
(cherry picked from commit 592b3bd066a47e38fa83499757960028c64db092)

commit_message:
Getting pacemaker node attribures and node status as dict.

def get_pacemaker_nodes_attributes(cibadmin_status_xml)
Adding possibility to parse 'cibadmin --query --scope status'.
Function return nested dictionary with node-fqdn and attribute name as keys.

def get_pcs_nodes(pcs_status_xml)
Adding possibility to parse 'pcs status xml'.
and return nested dictionary with node-fqdn and attribute name as keys.
They will be used in test for pacemaker resources when disk is full

Change-Id: Ieabef9eca1eff79ac504ae6df1e1a1409ed276ff
Closes-Bug: #1507721
Related-Bug: #1500446

commit_message:
Improve dry-ness of base dockerfile.j2

The delorean repositories no longer have a separate location for
openvswitch.  Now openvswitch is located in delorean-deps.repo
and the rest of delorean master is located in the delorean.repo
file.  These files can be installed for both RDO and SOURCE, but
not for RHOS.  This patch uses the install_metatype to make a
determination as to when to install these two repos.  In the
process, we can remove the source RPM installation.

Change-Id: Ieedddd9d7ee234b6acdb03f7043d57c18e024951
Closes-Bug: #1508326

commit_message:
Added MAINTAINERS to top-level repo directory

In a consensus reached in a proposal for code review process
change [1], and proposed team structure policy document [2],
adding MAINTAINERS files in repositories.

Please note, that this file is written in YAML format in order
to allow further automation around code review process.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-August/072406.html
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/225376/1

Change-Id: Ie2a55378038fb44588b099fd420049337cb910e2

"}, {'created': '2015-10-16 08:05:24.000000000', 'message': "Update Neutron Configuration for Liberty

This patch includes the updates to the configuration files for
Neutron for the Liberty release.

Files Removed:
 - rootwrap.d/nec-plugin.filters
 - rootwrap.d/ryu-plugin.filters

Upgrade Notes:
 - 'prevent_arp_spoofing' is now not set, which reverts the setting
   to the upstream default (which is True). This is a change from
   Kilo where we set it to 'False' by default to maintain behaviour
   with the setting from Kilo's initial state. This setting may be
   overridden using the standard configuration override mechanism.
 - In order for 'prevent_arp_spoofing' to work properly,
   'extension_drivers = port_security' has been set in ml2_conf.ini.
   Without this set, prevent_arp_spoofing will block all instance
   traffic.

Note:
 - The break out of the linuxbridge_agent.ini from ml2_conf.ini has
   not been completed due to the complexity of the tasks involved.
   As this is not required specifically for Liberty the current
   config implementation will remain in place. The break out of the
   ini files may be done in a subsequent patch.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact
Closes-Bug: #1482756
Implements: blueprint liberty-release
Change-Id: I879fd37db2e699bc3d48bcdd65ec7888b0f3f1a9

commit_message:
Update Neutron Configuration for Liberty

This patch includes the updates to the configuration files for
Neutron for the Liberty release.

Files Removed:
 - rootwrap.d/nec-plugin.filters
 - rootwrap.d/ryu-plugin.filters

Variables removed due to upstream deprecation:
 - neutron_l3_router_delete_namespaces
 - neutron_dhcp_delete_namespaces

Defaults changed to match new upstream defaults:
 - neutron_driver_network_scheduler
 - neutron_driver_quota

Upgrade Notes:
 - The LinuxBridge configuration has been seperated out from
   plugins/ml2/ml2_conf.ini to plugins/ml2/linuxbridge_agent.ini
 - prevent_arp_spoofing is now set to the upstream default, which
   is True.

DocImpact
UpgradeImpact
Closes-Bug: #1482756
Implements: blueprint liberty-release
Change-Id: I879fd37db2e699bc3d48bcdd65ec7888b0f3f1a9

commit_message:
Adds the 1st initial package for upstream infra packaging

openstack-pkg-tools is the one tool that is used for setting-up the
packaging build environment and scripts for doing the actual build.
So this is the first one which I am trying to add.

Change-Id: Ib07a89d1e1baf0c56343c32c5da680fca8153172

commit_message:
keystone/auth: make service description configurable

This commit adds the service description as a class parameter in order to allow
users to update from a previous version if the service description is changed
(incorrectly spelled or wrong description)

Change-Id: I5c8a8e62e886d4778b44176a85c00717e57500ee
Closes-Bug: #1468407

commit_message:
Use clouds.yaml from devstack for functional tests

devstack produces a file called clouds.yaml already with credentials in
it. Rather than producing our own config file to run functional tests,
just consume the clouds.yaml file that's already there.

Closes-Bug: #1507386
Change-Id: I82c071b2cd903b9578d1f2ec515882c815812692

commit_message:
Refactored filter implementation.

1) Previously filter() was used to remove
   empty fields which creates problem while
   calulating length.
2) respose.body is returning byte literal 
   string. So decode() function is used to
   convert it in simple string.

Change-Id: I5e36dcb0a7482b030ca249248b5cbf8d14142c04
Partially-Implements: blueprint mistral-py3

commit_message:
In gate functional testing

This runs the ansible playbooks to completion.

It does not validate that OpenStack is working yet, but it will ensure
Ansible did not break.

Additional gates will be needed for this and there is a patch in
project-config to handle that.

Change-Id: I7a24a704023cc8f19d42844636e9cb512060f693
backport: liberty
Partially-Implements: blueprint functional-testing-gate

commit_message:
Fix docker proxy config file not correctly seting on k8s master

In I19c92dc9b4fe195037b5ad4ca49b529cf6be4cfb , we added proxy for k8s cluster,
but it is not working on k8s master since master doesn't have
/etc/systemd/system/docker.service.d/ which is diffenect from minion.

Beside, this patch also improves hardcode filename in add_proxy.sh.

Closes-Bug: #1508279
Change-Id: I03cd504276e9ca99625b93452f832de406cd1fb7
Co-authored-by: Madhuri Kumari <madhuri.kumari@intel.com>

commit_message:
Remove stackforge IRC notification

Remove notification of changes for stackforge repos from gerritbot.
Remove channels from accessbot where all repos have been retired.

stackforge/compass-install was left in for now since the team wants to get
it reinstated.

Change-Id: I4c7ec7f34aef126e7490de5169eb33f094c7e84a

commit_message:
Stackforge retirement: Job cleanup

Remove all entries for retired stackforge projects from
zuul/layout.yaml, jenkins/projects/*.

Not removing networking-bgvpn and compass-install since the teams like
to revive those again.

Change-Id: Ie700d6986784de113d5f67f1f8f0df0016d66ed2

commit_message:
Port availability zones to core API

Changes:
- Register availability zones API as core API using old link.
- Remove extension code for availability zones.
- Leave rename of API url for future update which will be done with
  bump of microversion after port of all extensions to core API.

Partially implements bp ext-to-core

Change-Id: Ifc75ef2d16121634ad12e5e12960c928e4d24b90

No brainer imho - other projects like ironic use automaton and it's "one of ours" anyway so no big concerns around the new dependency imho.

If we don't want the dep - statemachines are dead simple - my first poc patch had an implementation of one from scratch. 

Overall +1 on this - not sure it even needed a spec.'}, {'account_id': 2243, 'date': '2015-10-15 14:28:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

We've had some of this in Cinder as well... but it's never really gone anywhere.  I'd be keen to see things progress in Nova and *borrow* some of it :)  

Depending on the details and how things go I could see some really useful shared patterns in this."}, {'account_id': 1063, 'date': '2015-10-15 19:27:43.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

I'd prefer using automaton instead of creating yet another state machine implementation. This has the advantage of sharing the pattern across other projects as well."}, {'account_id': 7461, 'date': '2015-10-19 11:00:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 1297, 'date': '2015-10-19 18:03:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

As the person who has been the primary developer of automaton I support using it, hopefully it helps and avoids people from creating there own similar things... If not, please contribute to make it fit better for u (vs creating another similar thing).

Anyone +1 one this, let's see where this goes."}, {'account_id': 1297, 'date': '2015-10-19 18:04:18.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

*Anyway +1 one this, let's see where this goes."}, {'account_id': 1297, 'date': '2015-10-19 21:52:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

With ease... That's useful for a variety of things IMHO."}, {'account_id': 14937, 'date': '2015-10-20 01:22:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Hi Joshua,

Thank you for the review.'}, {'account_id': 14937, 'date': '2015-10-20 02:46:39.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Referring to the Ironic state machine, I'll improve the spec to add more detail of the state machine. And then I think we can have better review of this. Please wait for a v2 spec."}, {'account_id': 5511, 'date': '2015-10-20 11:15:14.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I honestly don't see any reason to change this spec at all.

commit_message:
Update overcloud template description and Count constraints

Currently there's a vague list of services in the description, so instead
describe the roles supported for deployment, and encode the minimum allowed
of one Controller/Compute with zero Storage nodes in the parameter constraints.

Change-Id: Ib4917843f3e4770f0260db72719ed6af0ee8dc13

commit_message:
Allow setting custom ec2api port to listen to

The README mentions that install.sh allows setting
custom port(other than 8788 default) to start ec2api
on but upon looking, there wasnt any option. This patch
adds the option to allow user to set a different port
prior to installation using install.sh script.
also the options defined in devstack plugin but
it isnt being set in ec2api.conf.

Change-Id: I440b69fafb5555a7a9f4d1e27b1f811d2a3ecc29

commit_message:
Fix mistral dsvm gate

Because of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/235480/ path to
tempest conf now is defining in other way, need to export
special path and do not try to find tempest.conf using
relative path from test run directory.

Change-Id: I4de9d71332edab96e4d6c96f3b84f6ea2c459a67
(cherry picked from commit f8087961f611957c3e52239d8ecf064b922abf2c)

commit_message:
Change ports range in validators and test function

Current implementation for validating the port number and protocol
number accepts invalid values. For port number it accepts -1 which is
invalid, and the 0 which is used as programming technique for specifying
system-allocated (dynamic) ports. For protocol number it accepts only
one invalid value which is -1.

Proposed solution changes the range of:
- valid port numbers from <-1, 65535> to <1, 65535>
- valid protocol numbers from <-1, 255> to <0, 255>

Co-Authored-By: Wlodzimierz Borkowski <wlodek.borkowski@gmail.com>
Co-Authored-By: Kamil Rykowski <kamil.rykowski@intel.com>

Closes-Bug: 1329571
Closes-Bug: 1431367
Change-Id: I2dc83b611deaa0cc91d586dad1c01d8de91d1957

commit_message:
Add timeout for keystone client in proxy checker

Add 10 seconds timeout for Keystone client initialization
during HTTP proxy check, because otherwise it could hang
forever.
Also check that find_proxy returns IP address before
using it.

Change-Id: I4fabe0f5fee3d2acc3e7e2387ac858b2c56493c7
Closes-bug: #1499415

We don't need a separate script to wrap the oslo-config-generator. Like

define the namespaces.

Change-Id: Icc9b7b41baf89683c54f6aefcb3c4257f1e2f3d6

commit_message:
Using oslo-config-generator to instead of generate-config-file.sh

We don't need a separate script to wrap the oslo-config-generator. Like
other projects, we can just specify a config-generator config file to
define the namespaces.

Change-Id: Icc9b7b41baf89683c54f6aefcb3c4257f1e2f3d6

setuptools uses an .eggs folder as a cache to avoid multiple
downloads.  git should ignore this directory as it will never

Change-Id: I49714b769ce42d45cf14c4c8f4c10ae40e638f4b

commit_message:
Add .eggs/ to .gitignore

setuptools uses an .eggs folder as a cache to avoid multiple
downloads.  git should ignore this directory as it will never
be added to the repo.

Change-Id: I49714b769ce42d45cf14c4c8f4c10ae40e638f4b

commit_message:
Remove unused common files

As part of the move from DocBook XML to RST, some files in the common
directory become orphaned since there's now no guide including them.

Remove all these orphaned files.

Change-Id: Ife5e0c791bd4e7cbfcd720d1acf56a067b3a5b06

Disable test guests_state_on_host_boot

Such test was added to cover automatically  intsance resume issues,
but such issues is not affected kilo and liberty release,
so that we can disable this test

[{'created': '2015-10-19 12:44:58.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "DVR: Notify specific agent when update floatingip"

This reverts commit 52e91f48f2327b47f126893f9cb12f153380a9a6.

The patch broke notifications about FIP updates and triggered 100% gate
failures for Ironic gate.

I believe that I0cbe8c51c3714e6cbdc48ca37135b783f8014905 is also
breaking notifications, but for FIP create, which probably was not utilized in
any gate before and hence not caught in time.

I believe the author of the patch assumed that DVR mixin is not used for
legacy routers, while it is. And I wouldn't blame the author for such a
no-brainer assumption. The current L3/DVR code is such a mess that even
core reviewer team failed to catch the issue and merged it in.

The failure shows lots of issues with code quality, but also testing coverage.
Notifications to L3 agents should have been properly covered.

This does not answer the question why we get NotFound from database
on fetching a FIP router_id, but that's another issue that should be
investigated while Ironic gate is happy.

Change-Id: I4affac49d7c63f47c5654b94b28f4cb7471e87b0
Closes-Bug: #1507558

commit_message:
Revert "DVR: Notify specific agent when update floatingip"

This reverts commit 52e91f48f2327b47f126893f9cb12f153380a9a6.

The patch broke notifications about FIP updates and triggered 100%
gate failures for Ironic gate.

I believe that I0cbe8c51c3714e6cbdc48ca37135b783f8014905 is also
breaking notifications, but for FIP create, which probably was not
utilized in any gate before and hence not caught in time.

The change the reverted patch introduced made update_floatingip to
fetch router based on FIP router_id field on every call, which was
not the case before the patch. For some reason unknown at the
moment, we get NotFound from database on this fetch.

The patch does not answer the question why we get NotFound from
database on fetching a FIP router_id, but that's another issue that
should be investigated while Ironic gate is happy.

Change-Id: I4affac49d7c63f47c5654b94b28f4cb7471e87b0
Closes-Bug: #1507558
Related-Bug: #1507602

commit_message:
Replace github with openstack git repo

git.openstack.org is our official server, github is just a
read-only mirror.

Linking to github might also raise the expectation that we use the usual
github workflow which is not the case.

Change-Id: I3b3e8213c264757838c8e5fd33221eebf219cdc8

commit_message:
Don't download fedora-user as part of --all build

fedora-user is an optional image that is only used for testing the
deployed overcloud.  We shouldn't force everyone to download it as
part of the --all build when in many cases it won't be needed.  The
option to download it is left in the client though so it can still
be easily retrieved when necessary.

I minus 1 because I really think this has no need to be in nova.conf, should be addressed by the API'}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2015-04-29 13:29:37.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

@sahid - thanks for the feedback.  I called out the API approach as an alternative, but based on the operator feedback I've received, that is more than they're looking for--people want this to be more of a static/conf style setting.

In the spirit of not over-engineering a solution for this and introducing API changes, that is why the solution it proposed as is.  Doing it at the API layer would also have the 'negative' side of requiring every OpenStack management tool to have to change to capitalize on this capability as well (since nothing would use the new API); this conf option makes it easier to surface immediate benefit for operators."}, {'account_id': 7730, 'date': '2015-04-29 13:54:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Code-Review

Hum yes that the bad thing of updating API we have to make clients handle that new option. The main concern is about to make the operator blocked when he would like to resize an instance on a host which does not have enough disk capacity BUT I guess he always can migrate the instance and then resize it which result for me: "Updating the API is the way to follow".

Let see what think other contributors of the community so I prefer just 0 on it.'}, {'account_id': 782, 'date': '2015-05-11 09:45:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(6 comments)

Sorry, I don't understand the use case and problem you are defining here.

We need to be clear that resize is a user operation, and there seems to be some admin want for VMs not to move, that is not well described here.

Please can you elaborate on the use cases, to make the case for this feature. I really don't get the problem you are trying to solve, which is making it hard to recommend the solution.

This current propose seems odd, as in many cases all users will be unable to resize their VMs, if you use a fill first scheduler strategy. I don't see a good reason for this tradeoff yet."}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2015-05-11 23:21:47.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-11 23:26:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified+1

(1 comment)

I think this is improperly positioned as a "flexible scheduling of resize" thing, instead of what it really is, which is a new operation (in-place-resize) or a specific mode of the existing resize operation. Also, it duplicates the more appropriate (and older) spec here:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/141219/

I propose we abandon this in favor of the above review and make sure it has everything in it we need.'}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2015-05-17 04:47:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

(3 comments)

Dan, thanks for pointing out the similar spec review [1]. I agree, we should ensure that one simply entails the functional characteristics of what I was proposing here. Let's go that route for now... as such, I'll abandon this one and close the blueprint for now in favor of [1].

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/141219/"}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2015-05-17 04:48:44.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Abandoning in favor of a similar spec [1] as recommended by Dan.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/141219/'}, {'account_id': 7664, 'date': '2015-05-23 04:57:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

@Dan - if we close https://review.openstack.org/#/c/141219/ per the summit Etherpad, is it possible to reopen this - or would we close the whole idea of a 'live resize'?

Unfortunately I wasn't able to attend this particular session, so I didn't get a chance to hear if there were any final verdicts.

- Joe"}]

commit_message:
Proposal for Flexible Resize Scheduling

Provides additional flexibility for specifying how destination hosts are
selected for resize operations.

blueprint flexible-resize-behavior

Change-Id: Ie231b0bc40b6842cb459be57b55e673650f25edd

commit_message:
Add whitespaces between words of tempest.conf

There is missing space in 'help' sectionf of couple
of options in conf.py, so tempest.conf comes out to
be joined words with no space in them.

Change-Id: I4aa707edf528d48f17335d1df83215e15f830e4b

subject: Fix missing whitespace in conf help There is a missing whitespace between 'the' and 'admin' so in tempest.conf it turns out to be theadmin. Fix applied to config.py.

commit_message:
Fix missing whitespace in conf help
There is a missing whitespace between 'the'
and 'admin' so in tempest.conf it turns out to
be theadmin. Fix applied to config.py.

Change-Id: I72f95fd99db79d48c6bcadfd12f536901435e584
Author: hayderimran7<imran@cloudscaling.com>

commit_message:
Remove SUPPORTED_AGENT_TYPES for l2pop

In a world where agents can be out of tree,
this check seems no longer necessary.

As part of networking-vsphere project which runs ovsvapp agent
on each ESXi host inside service VM, which talk to neutron-server
having l2pop enabled in a multi-hypervisor mode like KVM, ESXi.
The tunnels are not getting established between KVM compute node
and ESXi host. The l2pop mech_driver needs to embrace ovsvapp agent
to form the tunnels.

Hence, this patch-set addresses the issue by removing the
SUPPORTED_AGENT_TYPES for l2pop.

Closes-Bug: #1507684
Change-Id: I93ca5736e4aad41b851d2b7b082b4bb69d1632fb

subject: ovs: ovs agent updates the wrong port when using Xen + Neutron Problem: When VM is under HVM mode, ovs will create two ports and two interfaces for a single virtual ethernet interface inside the VM: One is named as tapx.0 which is qemu-emulated NIC, used when no PV drivers installed; The other one is named as vifx.0 which is the xen network frontend NIC, used when VM has PV drivers installed. Depending on the PV driver's existing, either of the two ports/interfaces will be used. But current implement can NOT process multiple ports/interfaces. If it configures(e.g. set tag) one interface but the other one is in fact used by ovs; it will have network problem.

one tiny code change needed'}, {'account_id': 6735, 'date': '2015-10-12 10:46:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

I think we need a wider design discussion on the best fix here.
I understand that adding multiple ports causes a massive growth in the size of the patch, but it is the 'right' solution in this case, since a single VIF does have more than one port.

Using an 'active' port is OK, but introduces a race condition when not using the monitor daemon, since there can be a period of a few seconds where the TAP has been replaced with a VIF but before the agent updates the tags.

There are other options that we might consider, for example XenServer adding a patch-port which is returned as the main interface, so the tags are added to the patch-port then traffic forwarded to the appropriate VIF+TAP on the primary bridge?  Not sure if this would work.

Another option might be to re-think our OVS integration from scratch and send traffic through the Compute VM.  I assume we'd need to automatically create a new port in the Compute VM when a VIF is created, and create the patch of that port in  dom0 through to the VIF+TAP but this might also solve the vxlan tunnel endpoint issues, and give an architecture much closer to the KVM case."}, {'account_id': 6735, 'date': '2015-10-12 10:46:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1'}, {'account_id': 17920, 'date': '2015-10-12 15:56:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1 Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 17920, 'date': '2015-10-21 07:06:52.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

design changed; the new patch set is: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/237900/'}]

[{'created': '2015-10-12 06:07:34.000000000', 'message': 'ovs: ovs agent updates the wrong port when using Xen + Neutron
Problem:
When VM is under HVM mode, ovs will create two ports and two interfaces for
a single virtual ethernet interface inside the VM: One is named as tapx.0
which is qemu-emulated NIC, used when no PV drivers installed; The other
one is named as vifx.0 which is the xen network frontend NIC, used when
VM has PV drivers installed. Depending on the PV driver's existing,
either of the two ports/interfaces will be used. But current implement
can NOT process multiple ports/interfaces. If it configures(e.g. set tag)
one interface but the other one is in fact used by ovs; it will have
network problem.

Solution:
 There are two potential solutions:
 1. configure both ports regardless which port will be used by ovs; so
 both have the same configuration.
 2. if there are multiple choices, ovs set the filed of "iface-status" as
active for the one taking effective; and others will be inactive. So the
other solution is to return the active one only. If there is any
switchover happens in later phase, the returned ofport should be changed
as the ofport is uniq for each port. Then treat this port as updated and
then it will configure the new chosen port accordingly.
 As the existing relative functions is implemented basing on the
assumption that only one single port/interface exists for each virtual
interface inside the VM. With the 1st solution, it requires much more
effort to change the existing data structure to hold multiple
ports/interfaces and corresponding it will make things more complicated.
So the 2nd solution has been chosen within this patch set.

Change-Id: I06e5e9123731e01e04c5f7f15ef857703521adc7
Closes-Bug: #1268955

commit_message:
ovs: ovs agent updates the wrong port when using Xen + Neutron
Problem:
When VM is under HVM mode, ovs will create two ports and two interfaces for
a single virtual ethernet interface inside the VM: One is named as tapx.0
which is qemu-emulated NIC, used when no PV drivers installed; The other
one is named as vifx.0 which is the xen network frontend NIC, used when
VM has PV drivers installed. Depending on the PV driver's existing,
either of the two ports/interfaces will be used. But current implement
can NOT process multiple ports/interfaces. If it configures(e.g. set tag)
one interface but the other one is in fact used by ovs; it will have
network problem.

Solution:
 There are two potential solutions:
 1. configure both ports regardless which port will be used by ovs; so
 both have the same configuration.
 2. if there are multiple choices, ovs set the filed of "iface-status" as
active for the one taking effective; and others will be inactive. So the
other solution is to return the active one only. If there is any
switchover happens in later phase, the returned ofport should be changed
as the ofport is uniq for each port. Then treat this port as updated and
then it will configure the new chosen port accordingly.
 As the existing relative functions is implemented basing on the
assumption that only one single port/interface exists for each virtual
interface inside the VM. With the 1st solution, it requires much more
effort to change the existing data structure to hold multiple
ports/interfaces and corresponding it will make things more complicated.
So the 2nd solution has been chosen within this patch set.

Change-Id: I06e5e9123731e01e04c5f7f15ef857703521adc7
Closes-Bug: #1268955

commit_message:
Consolidate module constants.

3 separate places had hardcoded values for the t-h-t directory. Many
values are/will be shared, this patch consolidates them to avoid having
them diverge in the future.

Depends-On: I98e19cc29d69cbd6636cd4ce77a07c7a0e3dc048
Change-Id: I205569f4be0bcee2b284048dec7ddf0b28bbd8a1

I like the change but it seems DIB will check for twice this size [1]?

And yet I've seen image building going OOM with 12G as well because the undercloud had 3 cores.

I wonder if we shouldn't disable it completely or set an even higher minimum, like 12 to enable it only when we have plenty of RAM? Thoughts?

https://github.com/openstack/diskimage-builder/blob/3972510d20a85932da925411be4edf9790757274/lib/common-functions#L24"}, {'account_id': 6928, 'date': '2015-10-16 20:00:16.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Yeah, it checks for double the total RAM because by default tmpfs uses half of the available RAM.  So with 8 GB of total RAM, you get a 4 GB tmpfs.

I have to say I've never had a 12 gig overcloud OOM during image builds, and I give mine 8 cores.  That said, this behavior doesn't seem to be entirely consistent, so I'd be open to increasing the limit to 16 GB.  I'd prefer not to disable it completely because you do take a bit of a performance hit building without tmpfs, at least by my completely subjective tests.  Of course, I never have a 16 GB undercloud so I guess it would be all the same from my perspective. :-)"}, {'account_id': 7065, 'date': '2015-10-19 13:49:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 9712, 'date': '2015-10-21 06:49:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-10-21 06:49:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

[{'created': '2015-10-14 16:03:23.000000000', 'message': "Set --min-tmpfs for overcloud-full build

I consistently have problems building images on an 8 GB VM with
the undercloud already installed (which is the documented flow).
At 4 or 12 GB it works fine, but 8 seems to fall in a sweet spot
where the tmpfs usage of dib causes OOM problems.  4 GB works
because dib doesn't use tmpfs by default with that little memory,
and 12 GB seems to be sufficient to avoid running out of memory
even with tmpfs.

This changes passes the --min-tmpfs 5 parameter to the image build
for the overcloud-full image (the largest image by far) so it will
not attempt to build in tmpfs if there is less than 12 GB of RAM.
5 instead of 6 because due to rounding 6 would result in tmpfs not
being used on 12 GB VMs either (similar to how it is not used on a
4 GB VM even though the default is 2).

Note that tmpfs by default uses half of total memory, which is why
all of the min-tmpfs numbers are half of the expected memory on the
system.

Change-Id: I6254d04216936551e68ac02999f2bffc11b19f65

commit_message:
Set --min-tmpfs for overcloud-full build

I consistently have problems building images on an 8 GB VM with
the undercloud already installed (which is the documented flow).
At 4 or 12 GB it works fine, but 8 seems to fall in a sweet spot
where the tmpfs usage of dib causes OOM problems.  4 GB works
because dib doesn't use tmpfs by default with that little memory,
and 12 GB seems to be sufficient to avoid running out of memory
even with tmpfs.

This changes passes the --min-tmpfs 5 parameter to the image build
for the overcloud-full image (the largest image by far) so it will
not attempt to build in tmpfs if there is less than 12 GB of RAM.
5 instead of 6 because due to rounding 6 would result in tmpfs not
being used on 12 GB VMs either (similar to how it is not used on a
4 GB VM even though the default is 2).

Note that tmpfs by default uses half of total memory, which is why
all of the min-tmpfs numbers are half of the expected memory on the
system.

Change-Id: I6254d04216936551e68ac02999f2bffc11b19f65

commit_message:
Add HTTPS to image location help text

Glance supports http/https url, but the help text and description
only reference http.

Closes-Bug: #1495976
Change-Id: I7e09e06882e5b9f995013756f972eb0b0b33f7f3

commit_message:
Install Guide Cleanup

This commit does the following:

- sets all shell prompts in code-blocks to the root prompt
- uses shell-session code-block since the shell prompt was being
  treated as a comment
- links configure-aodh.rst in configure.rst (running tox was
  complaining that this file wasn't being linked anywhere)
- other minor cleanup

Change-Id: I9e3ac8bb0cabd1cc17952cfd765dbb0d8f7b6fa2

commit_message:
Fix mistral dsvm gate

Because of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/235480/ path to
tempest conf now is defining in other way, need to export
special path and do not try to find tempest.conf using
relative path from test run directory.

Change-Id: I4de9d71332edab96e4d6c96f3b84f6ea2c459a67

Fix Debian install of Horizon in Debian

Adds a note about the new /horizon Alias in the Debian liberty package,
plus make sure the Finalize section is also present in Debian.

commit_message:
Make Ceph install from Source on RPM

Ceph doesnt install from source on RPM because Ceph pulls in
python-requests.  This causes a cpio error during unpacking
because requests is installed in the base image.  A simple
workaround is to remove in the nova-compute container which
is the only container this conflict occurs within.

backport: liberty

Change-Id: I493900854a53c98f1a5cb6478675a18feceefea5
Closes-Bug: #1508236
(cherry picked from commit 194bb93ff26cfda92ff79742d361350a353ecacd)

commit_message:
Fixed typo in getting started doc

commit_message:
Add option to generate sample conf file.

The README says you can generate it :
https://github.com/openstack/senlin/blob/master/etc/senlin/README-senlin.conf.txt
but this option was missing.
This patch allows user to use `tox -egenconfig` to directly
generate a sample conf file in etc/senlin/senlin.conf.sample.
This helps in vetting any doubts if the already given conf is
outdated or has incorrect config options.

Change-Id: I6f8aa4cd9fd7f5296997469f04a333d67e9ddbd5

This patch reverts commit dea4c2cce33b6a6f0d18caca485be89e82ed51c0.

Our tempest job has been passing, but OVN itself is going through some
*major* changes quite rapidly, and it's a bumpy ride adapting
networking-ovn to those changes.  We need to update networking-ovn to
use OVN's new support for ACLs (security groups), distributed routing,
and more.  It will be much easier if we can work through all of that in
several patches and then turn voting back on.

Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Revert "Make gate-tempest-dsvm-networking-ovn voting"

This patch reverts commit dea4c2cce33b6a6f0d18caca485be89e82ed51c0.

Our tempest job has been passing, but OVN itself is going through some
*major* changes quite rapidly, and it's a bumpy ride adapting
networking-ovn to those changes.  We need to update networking-ovn to
use OVN's new support for ACLs (security groups), distributed routing,
and more.  It will be much easier if we can work through all of that in
several patches and then turn voting back on.

Change-Id: If54532c79d1331f2154ed74697ce0e46fd652e91
Signed-off-by: Russell Bryant <rbryant@redhat.com>

commit_message:
[Contributor Guide] RST section finished

1. Adds the following subsections:
   * Introduction to RST
   * Tables
   * Images
   * Profiling
   * Lists
   * Inline markups
   * Decorations
   * Commenting
2. Restructures the toc
3. Creates separate files for each subsection included in the
RST-related folder for simpler maintenance.

Change-Id: I08568fb37755109552edf9692b8f259660550a69

In my testing, the GPG key takes approximately 50 seconds to download

the Ceph GPG sign key.  Crank up the timer to 90 seconds so the key

commit_message:
Increase Ceph RPM gpg key timeout to 90 seconds

The default timeout for Ceph GPG rpm key retrieval is 30 seconds.
In my testing, the GPG key takes approximately 50 seconds to download
often resulting in a failure to build containers that need to retrieve
the Ceph GPG sign key.  Crank up the timer to 90 seconds so the key
is more likely to be downloaded, allowing images to be built.

backport: liberty

TrivialFix

Change-Id: I7420cdf8d3b61aa9f4f52795fccbe5da3e48d57b
(cherry picked from commit a026ec253a616aa147cff72f43a38eda90789b0a)

commit_message:
Make Ceph install from Source on RPM

Ceph doesnt install from source on RPM because Ceph pulls in
python-requests.  This causes a cpio error during unpacking
because requests is installed in the base image.  A simple
workaround is to remove in the nova-compute container which
is the only container this conflict occurs within.

backport: liberty

Change-Id: I493900854a53c98f1a5cb6478675a18feceefea5
Closes-Bug: #1508236

'}, {'created': '2015-10-02 16:45:13.000000000', 'message': 'Split the FIP Namespace delete in L3 agent for DVR

Right now we are seeing a race condition in the l3 agent
for DVR routers when a floatingip is deleted and created.

The agent tries to delete the floatingip namespace and
while it tries to delete there is another call to add a
namespace. There is a timing windows in between these two
calls were sometimes the call to create a namespace succeeds
but, when tried to execute any commands in the namespace
it fails, since the namespace was deleted concurrently.

Since the fip namespace is associated with an external net
and each compute node has only one fip namespace, we would
like to only delete the fip namespace when the external net
is deleted.

The first step is to split the delete functionality into two.
The call to delete will only remove the dependency that
the fipnamespace has with the router namespace such as fpr and
rfp veth pairs.

The call to cleanup_fip_namespace will actually delete the
the fip namespace and the fg device.

commit_message:
Split the FIP Namespace delete in L3 agent for DVR

Right now we are seeing a race condition in the l3 agent
for DVR routers when a floatingip is deleted and created.

The agent tries to delete the floatingip namespace and
while it tries to delete there is another call to add a
namespace. There is a timing window in between these two
calls where sometimes the call to create a namespace succeeds
but, when tried to execute any commands in the namespace
it fails, since the namespace was deleted concurrently.

Since the fip namespace is associated with an external net
and each node has only one fip namespace for an external net,
we would like to only delete the fip namespace when the
external net is deleted.

The first step is to split the delete functionality into two.
The call to fip_ns.cleanup will only remove the dependency that
the fipnamespace has with the router namespace such as fpr and
rfp veth pairs.

The call to fip_ns.delete will actually delete the
the fip namespace and the fg device.

Partial-Bug: #1501873
Change-Id: Ic94625d5a968f554af70c274b2b2c20ab64e2487

commit_message:
Ensure we log exceptions on 500 responses

When running the api server under a real wsgi container the exceptions
aren't being propagated to the log file. This makes debugging a 500
error very difficult. This commit adds the option to the flask app
to ensure that we propagate tracebacks into the log.

Change-Id: Ibc4be9f98aaf3e6cb17ccaa39095ad52ebdada35

commit_message:
Add parameter --tests-file to 'verify start'

With this parameter it is possible to load a list of tests from a file.

Closes-bug: #1450478

Change-Id: I576db470a7253151ed6753da4035a2f235278a39

commit_message:
Make webhook related DB query project safe

This patch makes webhook related DB queries project safe by default.
The load method of webhook module is also changed to add project_safe
parameter.

Change-Id: I071b2b741deee0d762f7bd0b121c17e6dce7f0fb
Implements: blueprint make-db-query-project-safe

commit_message:
Make trigger related DB queries project safe

This patch makes trigger related DB queries project safe by default.
load() method of trigger base module is also revised to add
project_safe input parameter.

Change-Id: Ie7a106e76e706ab943baee3e297ad8d793bed85b
Implements: blueprint make-db-query-project-safe

commit_message:
Make event related DB queries project safe

This patch makes event related DB queries project safe by default.
load() method in event module is also changed to add project_safe
input parameter.

TODO:
 - Add test case for event module.

Change-Id: I68cdac1da472665ae53d355734931f4a526d2ced
Implements: blueprint make-db-query-project-safe

commit_message:
REST Amp Agent: Compare lower case MAC Addresses

When the post_plug_vip method is called on the rest amphora driver,
the agent on the amphora running the rest server attempts to find the
interface by the MAC address passed in through the API. On some OSes
the interfaces returned by the OS has the mac address in all lower case,
whereas the MAC address passed in through the API is in upper case.
Just lower() both and then compare.

Closes-Bug: #1507881
Change-Id: I4ddfd25911d31285513009432f80da080196e8b2

commit_message:
Change Identity API default version to 3

Devstack now issues all v3 OSC commands for our CI, and since v3
has everything v2 has, we should be able to switch to v3.

Furthermore, most OSC users were initially  using OSC since they
were looking to exploit v3 keystone capabilities.

Change-Id: If7de86946f6dd0f148aa5f526155cccf90adfcc3

In Glance there has been some work around adding Elastic Search capabilities:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/138051/9/specs/kilo/catalog-index-service.rst

There was a desire to add these capabilities to allow searching things besides images (instances, volumes etc), and so a new project "OpenStack Searchlight" is in the process of being set up:

https://launchpad.net/searchlight

There was some discussion at the summit about potentially aligning these efforts.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-06-11 09:17:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

commit_message:
Properly handle segmentation_id in OVS agent

The segmentation_id of a OVS VLAN can be None, but a recent change
assumed that it was always an integer. It highlighted the fact that we
try to store None in the OVS database, which got stored as a string.
This fixes the storage, and handles loading the value while keeping
compatibility.

Change-Id: I6e7df1406c90ddde254467bb87ff1507a4caaadd
Closes-Bug: #1494281

@Boris, we can not just remove this check from delete_environment method, because we have two possible situations: when we delete empty environment, in this case actually we do not need to wait for environment deletion, because as @Victor said, it takes no time, another case is deletion of deployed environment, this takes some time (it includes deletion of stack), we need to wait. 

According current implementation of wait_for_status we have to pass ready_statuses, such as "deleted" to check that item was deleted, but murano environment does not have such status, so when we try to call latest_status = get_status(resource, status_attr) for not deployed murano env it cases an 404 error, because for this moment env was already deleted, it doesn't exists in DB anymore, so we can't get 'deleted' status. 

This patch was made to handle such situation.'}, {'account_id': 8592, 'date': '2015-10-14 14:50:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

commit_message:
Prevent false negative results during wait for resource deletion

This patch replaces get_status for latest_status to None value
to prevent 404 NotFound exception, if resource removed faster, than
wait code will interpreted.
Change-Id: I4f3baaf01e14d4794ce675ad37b300b876b9fc12

commit_message:
Support private address override in inventory

ansible inventory supports a command line switch --private which
overrides the clouds.yaml setting. Support passing it in.

Change-Id: I74bf98be26b605a5e9ac74ab478f421c39616d74

commit_message:
Revert "Match on dsvm-fedora-22 and dsvm-f21 nodes"

This reverts commit 29a714741b24c1247dfaf9fd2863fce3d8438602.

There is only one fedora node type, "fedora-22".  I think the
NOT_REGISTERED errors from the puppet jobs might have been related to
a zuul reload around the same time.

Change-Id: Ie8d6b9d1f9840627ada0e18d4a725b475be6d3ce
